            "id": "668ea2f736c64382ad0b3",
            "questionText": "A construction manager is calculating the amount of concrete needed for a new foundation. The measurements obtained using a laser distance meter are: length = $!$12.550\\,m$!$, width = $!$8.200\\,m$!$, and depth = $!$0.300\\,m$!$. It is known that the laser meter consistently reads $!$5\\,mm$!$ short due to miscalibration. Calculate the actual volume of the concrete foundation in cubic metres, ensuring that the final answer is presented with the appropriate number of significant figures based on the precision of the measurements.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "4a68847c52534b72811d3",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the correction value needed in metres for a reading error of 5 mm. Please identify the correct conversion factor from millimetres to metres.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.005"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "97df9a78-627f-40ae-8aef-c68ba9dd9ec7"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$5 \\times 10^{-3}\\,m$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$5 \\times 10^{-2}\\,m$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$0.5\\,m$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ca047a6b01ff4d3db9989",
                    "stepText": "Now, each measurement must be corrected by adding this conversion value. Which process correctly explains how to adjust a measurement that is consistently underread by a fixed amount?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "3474184d-fe1b-4c7e-b1c3-103625088cef"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "Corrected measurement = measured value + correction",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "Corrected measurement = measured value - correction",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "Corrected measurement = measured value \\times correction",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "629f94f7bef64c92bcfdb",
                    "stepText": "After applying the correction of $!$0.005\\,m$!$, the dimensions become: length = $!$12.550 + 0.005 = 12.555\\,m$!$, width = $!$8.200 + 0.005 = 8.205\\,m$!$, and depth = $!$0.300 + 0.005 = 0.305\\,m$!$. Next, identify the correct formula to calculate the volume of a rectangular block.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "5019a5fa-0ef6-41b7-9c92-8a9c074870d4"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V = length \\times width \\times depth$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V = length + width + depth$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V = \\frac{length \\times width}{depth}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
